## Accessibility for Mathematical Content

### Screen Reader Support
```typescript
// Provide descriptive alt text for equations
<span aria-label="Force equals mass times acceleration">
  <MathMarkdown content="\\[ F = ma \\]" />
</span>

// Use semantic markup for physics problems
<div role="math" aria-label="Kinematic equation: velocity equals initial velocity plus acceleration times time">
  <MathMarkdown content="\\[ v = v_0 + at \\]" />
</div>
```

### Text Alternatives
```typescript
// Always provide text descriptions alongside visual math
<div className="physics-equation">
  <MathMarkdown content="\\[ KE = \\frac{1}{2}mv^2 \\]" />
  <p className="sr-only">
    Kinetic energy equals one half times mass times velocity squared
  </p>
</div>
```

## Performance Optimization

### Lazy Loading KaTeX
The MathMarkdown component already handles lazy loading:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const loadKatex = async () => {
    const katex = await import('katex')
    // Render math expressions
  }
  loadKatex()
}, [content])
```

### Caching Rendered Math
```typescript
const mathCache = new Map<string, string>()

const renderMath = useMemo(() => {
  if (mathCache.has(content)) {
    return mathCache.get(content)
  }
  
  const rendered = katex.renderToString(content, options)
  mathCache.set(content, rendered)
  return rendered
}, [content])
```

## Common Physics Patterns

### Problem Structure
```typescript
interface PhysicsProblem {
  given: string[]          // Known values
  find: string            // What to solve for
  diagram?: string        // Scenario image URL
  solution: {
    steps: string[]       // Solution steps
    finalAnswer: {
      value: number
      unit: string
      significantFigures: number
    }
  }
}
```

### Unit Conversion Support
```typescript
const unitConversions = {
  length: { m: 1, cm: 0.01, mm: 0.001, km: 1000 },
  time: { s: 1, min: 60, hr: 3600 },
  mass: { kg: 1, g: 0.001 },
  force: { N: 1, kN: 1000 }
}

const convertUnits = (value: number, fromUnit: string, toUnit: string, category: string): number => {
  const conversions = unitConversions[category]
  return (value * conversions[fromUnit]) / conversions[toUnit]
}
```